cs.SC, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms for computing the factors of polynomials. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper mentions a polynomial-time algorithm. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper presents a new Gap Theorem. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper discusses the complexity of testing whether a polynomial is identically zero. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but it is mentioned in the abstract that the algorithm can be partially extended to other situations such as absolute and approximate factorizations, which could fall under this category.
